This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with visual saliency detection, which is a fundamental problem in computer vision. The use of deep convolutional neural networks (CNNs) also suggests that it may belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the neural network architecture and feature extraction techniques used in the paper may also make it relevant to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the construction of a new large database of images may make it relevant to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
